From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 16:32:03 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 35/64] web-app: chat export viewer pins the chat background to
 the viewport
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The app paints the chat background pattern on
.message-list-and-composer, which is viewport-sized in the app — but in
the exported viewer that element grows with the whole message list, so
background-size: cover scaled the pattern up to the full chat height
(comically large for long chats). The export now paints color + image
on a position:fixed, viewport-sized ::before layer (mobile browsers
handle that reliably, unlike background-attachment: fixed) and clears
the background from the growing container, so the pattern renders at
its normal density and stays static while scrolling — in the viewer
and in the single-file snapshot alike.
---
 .../components/dialogs/ExportChatToHtml.tsx   | 22 ++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/packages/frontend/src/components/dialogs/ExportChatToHtml.tsx b/packages/frontend/src/components/dialogs/ExportChatToHtml.tsx
index 2831d57..5fe63a8 100644
--- a/packages/frontend/src/components/dialogs/ExportChatToHtml.tsx
+++ b/packages/frontend/src/components/dialogs/ExportChatToHtml.tsx
@@ -262,7 +262,27 @@ async function collectCss(): Promise<string> {
  * document is one long scrollable page with a sticky chat header */
 const EXPORT_CSS = `
 body { margin: 0; }
-.html-export .message-list-and-composer { min-height: 100vh; box-sizing: border-box; }
+/* the app paints the chat background on .message-list-and-composer, which is
+ * viewport-sized there — in the export that element grows with the whole
+ * chat, so background-size: cover would blow the pattern up to the full
+ * document height. Paint it on a fixed viewport-sized layer instead (a
+ * position:fixed pseudo-element; background-attachment: fixed is unreliable
+ * on mobile), so it stays put while scrolling. */
+body.html-export::before {
+  content: '';
+  position: fixed;
+  inset: 0;
+  z-index: -1;
+  background-color: var(--chatViewBg);
+  background-image: var(--chatViewBgImgPath);
+  background-size: cover;
+}
+.html-export .message-list-and-composer {
+  min-height: 100vh;
+  box-sizing: border-box;
+  background-color: transparent;
+  background-image: none;
+}
 .html-export #message-list {
   position: static;
   overflow-y: visible;
